The troops of the Nigerian Army, have foiled attempted attack by the Boko Haram terrorists, along Gashua road in Damaturu, Yobe state. Locals who spoke to ChannelsTV, said the insurgents were sighted around 5.00pm on Sunday, along Babangida town, the headquarters of Tarmuwa local government and advancing to the state capital. Lt. Chinonso Oteh, acting Assistant Director, Army Public Relations, Sector 2, Operation Lafiya Dole, confirmed that the planned attacks were repelled.